# CPSY 1950 Course Site Context

## Overview

CPSY 1950: Deep Learning in Brains, Minds & Machines — Jekyll course site at `https://thomas-serre.com/cpsy1950/`

## Active Files (Used)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `cpsy1950/index.md` | **Canonical** main course page — schedule, readings, links. All published content lives here. |
| `cpsy1950/syllabus.md` | Full syllabus (linked from index and sidebar) |
| `cpsy1950/PLANNING.md` | Internal planning only — excluded from site. Instructor notes, todos, draft ideas. |
| `_data/cpsy1950/structure.yml` | Sidebar navigation — parts, lessons, resources (Ed Discussion, Canvas) |
| `_layouts/course-sidebar.html` | Layout for all course pages |

## Sidebar Structure (structure.yml)

- **Course Information:** Overview (#overview), Schedule (#schedule), Syllabus
- **Weekly Schedule:** Links to #week1 through #week15 on index
- **Resources:** Ed Discussion, Canvas (external links)

## Editing Content

- **Schedule / readings / assignments:** Edit `cpsy1950/index.md` — this is the canonical source. All changes that affect students go here.
- **Sidebar links:** Edit `_data/cpsy1950/structure.yml`
- **Syllabus:** Edit `cpsy1950/syllabus.md`
- **Planning (internal only):** Edit `cpsy1950/PLANNING.md` — excluded from site. Use for instructor notes, todos, draft ideas.

## Unused Data Files

`_data/cpsy1950/readings.yml`, `schedule.yml`, `assignments.yml`, `videos.yml` exist but are **not used** by any page. The index has all content inline. These can be removed or kept for future refactoring.

## Build & Deploy

- Local: `bundle exec jekyll serve`
- Deploy: Push to GitHub; GitHub Pages rebuilds automatically

## Mandatory: Digital Accessibility (Brown University)

**Every change to the course site must not break digital accessibility.** Brown requires full compliance by May 2026. Reference: https://digital-accessibility.brown.edu/

Before committing any edit to `cpsy1950/` or `_layouts/course-sidebar.html`:

1. **Headings:** Single `<h1>` per page; logical nesting (h1 > h2 > h3); never skip levels
2. **Links:** Descriptive link text; external links use `target="_blank"` with `rel="noopener noreferrer"` and `title="Opens in new tab"`
3. **Images/iframes:** Every `<img>` has alt text; every `<iframe>` (e.g., YouTube embeds) has a `title` attribute
4. **Structure:** Landmarks (header, nav, main, footer); `lang="en-US"` on html
5. **Interactive:** All controls reachable via keyboard; visible focus styles

Root `.cursorrules` has full WCAG 2.1 AA checklist. Run Lighthouse accessibility audit before deploy.
